---
name: test
description: Run tests smartly — detect changed files and run only relevant tests
user-invocable: true
allowed-tools:
  - Bash(git *)
  - Bash(npm test *)
  - Bash(npm run test *)
  - Bash(pnpm test *)
  - Bash(pnpm run test *)
  - Bash(uv run pytest *)
  - Read
  - Glob
---

Run tests intelligently based on what changed:

1. Run `git diff --name-only HEAD` and `git diff --name-only --staged` to find changed files.
2. Identify which test files correspond to the changes (colocated tests, mirrored test directories, or related modules).
3. Run only the relevant tests first. If they pass, report success.
4. If no specific test mapping is clear, fall back to running the full test suite.
5. Report results: passed/failed count, and show failure details if any.
